        <div><h2>Purpose</h2>
            <p>Code for Good West Michigan (“Code for Good”, “we”, “us”, and “our”) is a Michigan nonprofit corporation. We are a volunteer-run collective of technology professionals dedicated to creating technical solutions for nonprofit agencies. We depend on volunteers like you who are experts in software development, design and other fields who desire to donate their time to nonprofits in order to create custom software to further their charitable missions. In turn, those nonprofits create meaningful change here in Grand Rapids and around the globe. In order to ensure that the beneficiaries of our work will have the necessary rights to use the software we create, it is important for us to establish a clear understanding of our respective rights and our beneficiaries’ rights in the software that you contribute. For this reason, you and Code for Good hereby agree as follows:</p>
