                <li>“Beneficiary Materials” means Materials owned or licensed by a Beneficiary and all Intellectual Property rights therein.</li>
                <li>“Code for Good Materials” means Materials owned or licensed by Code for Good and all Intellectual Property rights therein.</li>
                <li>“Confidential Information” means all nonpublic information of or about Code for Good or any Beneficiary, including any trade secrets, logins, and passwords, as well as any internal data, processes, and strategies, including financial and marketing information.</li>
                <li>“Intellectual Property” means (i) patents, patent disclosures and inventions (whether patentable or not), (ii) trademarks, service marks, trade dress, trade names, logos, corporate names, and domain names, whether registered or unregistered, and, in each case, associated goodwill, (iii) copyrights and copyrightable works (including computer programs), and rights in data and databases, whether registered or unregistered, (iv) trade secrets, know-how, and other Confidential Information, and (v) all other intellectual property rights whether registered or unregistered and including all applications for, and renewals or extensions of, such rights, and all similar or equivalent rights or forms of protection in any part of the world.</li>
                <li>“Materials” means source code, object code, documentation, data, know-how, technology, methods, designs, specifications, prototypes, and other materials relevant to the production of software and information systems.</li>
                <li>“Your Contributions” means Your Work Product and any of Your Materials that are incorporated into software or information systems produced by or under the direction of Code for Good or in the course of Code for Good events and activities.</li>
                <li>“Your Materials” means Materials owned or licensed by you and all Intellectual Property rights therein, including Materials produced, acquired, or licensed by you apart from your participation in Code for Good events and activities in any form.</li>
                <li>“Your Work Product” means Materials produced by you, alone or jointly with others, in the course of a Project.</li>
            </ul>
